<h2>JavaScript Number Methods</h2>

<p>The toString() method converts a Boolean to a string.</p>

<p id="demo"></p>
<p id="demo1"></p>

<script>
var x = false; // x is Boolean
   document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML ="The data type of x before conversion is:"  +typeof(x);
   document.getElementById("demo1").innerHTML ="The data type of x after conversion is:" +typeof(x.toString());
 
</script>

